    <section id="id-763977568147">
      <title>Short Menus</title>
      <para id="id4371695">The following examples of five-course, four-course, and three-course menus illustrate that even today's short menus follow the same se­quence based on the classical thirteen-course French menu. The individ­ual courses, however, have been merged in many cases. The original main course consisted of an entire, uncarved poultry, meat, or game animal - a whole prime rib of beef, for example. Today the entree has merged with the main course. The vegetable, at one time a separate course, today is served as a side dish with the main course. Cold appetizers are always served before the soup. Hot appetizers are served after the soup.</para>
